details.description:
Jordan Brand brought back one of the first Air Jordan 13 colorways with the release of the Jordan 13 Retro Flint (2020), now available on StockX. With previous retros in 2005 and 2010, this is the third time that the Jordan 13 Flint has been reintroduced.

This Jordan 13 Retro consists of a navy mesh and white leather upper with flint grey suede underlays. A Jumpman holograph on the ankle, 3M detailing throughout the upper, and Carolina blue branding on the tongue completes the design. These sneakers released in May of 2020 and retailed for $190 USD.

The Jordan 13 Retro Blue Gray updates the classic Jordan 13 Retro silhouette with blue/gray accents against a Crisp White base.

The upper is made of white, tumbled leather with blue/gray panels crafted from synthetic suede. The velvety texture of the synthetic suede contrasts the quilted design across the uppers. The outsole draws inspiration from a panther’s paw, featuring a pod design that grips the ground without sacrificing flexibility. Like other Air Jordan 13 Retro models, the "Blue Gray" version features a Zoom Air unit in the heel and forefoot. There is also a holographic eye on the heel that is secured by reinforced stitching.

Our experts at StockX like the way the Yellow Ochre details on the Jumpman logo and ‘JORDAN’ logo tag match splashes of color on the rubber outsole. The Jordan 13 Retro Blue Gray was released on February 10th, 2024, and retailed at $200.

name: Jordan 13 Retro Gym Red Flint Grey

details.description:
Jordan flipped one of the most popular Jordan 13 colorways of all time to create a new colorway with the Air Jordan 13 Red Flint. The Red Flint draws its inspiration from the often re-issued Air Jordan 13 Flint, remixing to the iconic colorway.

The Air Jordan 13 Red Flint features an upper made of red reflective mesh, white leather, and Flint Durabuck. In line with Jordan 13s of the past, a holographic Jumpman emblem is displayed on the lateral ankle. An embroidered Jumpman insignia on the tongue, and a Flint and white sole complete this Jordan 13.

The Jordan 13 Red Flint released in April of 2021 and retailed for $190.

Jordan Brand reimagines one of the original Air Jordan 13 Low colorways as a high-top with the Air Jordan 13 Brave Blue.

Drawing inspiration from the 1998 Air Jordan 13 Low Navy, the Air Jordan 13 Brave Blue features a black tumbled leather upper with Brave Blue mesh overlays and black Durabuck underlays. At the collar, a Jumpman hologram commemorates the design's signature styling. A sculptural white and black EVA foam sole provides support for daily wear.

The Air Jordan 13 Brave Blue released in April of 2022 and retailed for $200.

The Jordan 13 Retro Playoffs are making another return in 2023, its first appearance since its last retro in 2011. Michael Jordan debuted the Air Jordan 13 Playoffs in the 1998 NBA All-Star game, and continued to wear the sneakers throughout the season en route to his record breaking sixth NBA championship.
​
​Tinker Hatfield's original design for the Jordan 13 was inspired by Jordan’s aggressive play style, which was referred to as a Black Cat. The retro sneaker features black leather uppers, suede mudguards, and holographic eyes that sit below each collar.
​
​The Air Jordan 13 Retro Playoffs (2023) released February 18, 2023, with a retail price of $210.

The Air Jordan 13 Court Purple could serve as a dark variation of the 2019 Air Jordan 13 Lakers. In a similar styling, it features a black reflective textile and Court Purple Durabuck upper with a tumbled leather toe wrap and classic Jumpman hologram. A matching midsole and sculptural outsole complete the retro design.

The Air Jordan 13 Court Purple released in January of 2021 and retailed for $190.

The Jordan 13 Retro Dune Red reintroduces the Air Jordan 13 Retro silhouette with an updated combination of colors and materials.

Instead of tumbled or pebbled leather, the dimpled overlays are a texturized textile in Dune Red. In addition, the upper is synthetic leather and microfiber, which provide a softer finish than animal-derived materials can produce. Terra Blush accents are on the microfiber and a panel along the midsole. Like other Jordan 13 Retro models, this version displays the signature holographic eye on the medial heel. In terms of branding, the padded tongue boasts a Jumpman logo in Dune Red, and the area beneath the laces houses a Dune Red "JORDAN" logo tag with white lettering.

Our StockX experts like the paw-like outsole, which pays tribute to Michael Jordan’s "Black Cat" alter ego. The Jordan 13 Retro Dune Red was released on June 25, 2024, and retailed at $210.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro University Blue takes on the "Black Cat" silhouette that debuted in 1998.

The upper of this Retro Air Jordan 13 sneaker features black mesh and leather with blue suede overlays. The black tongue and black insole each feature a blue Jumpman and the toe box sports Jordan branding at the bottom of the laces. The panther eye on the lateral-side collar has a holographic finish. The blue midsole has black curving up onto it from the outsole. The outsole, designed to look like a panther paw, features Jumpman and AIR units.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro University Blue was released on December 23rd, 2022 at $200 retail.

Jordan Brand added a new colorway to their catalog with the Jordan 13 Lucky Green. The Lucky Green colorway is fairly reminiscent of the Jordan 13 Ray Allen PE that surfaced in 2011.

The Jordan 13 Lucky Green features a white leather upper with green suede overlays and 3M piping. A signature Jumpman holographic emblem on the ankle, perforated white leather tongue, and black and white sole add the finishing touches on this 1990s marvel. These sneakers released in September of 2020 and retailed for $190.

The Jordan 13 Retro in Wolf Gray is a men’s basketball shoe that provides comfort and protective padding both on and off the court. The sleek look of the shoe makes it appropriate for wear both during the game and during the after-party.

The Retro Jordan 13 in Wolf Gray has a clean white leather base with small perforations in the shape of a circle for a unique look. Wolf Gray overlays adorn the heel and the midsole just above the sole of the shoe. It features a vibrant red color underfoot, and the Jordan Jumpman logo appears in the same red shade on the tongue. Branding details are completed with the signature Jordan hologram on the back.

What we at StockX think makes this shoe stand out is its unique, perforated, white leather base. This element gives the shoe a spotless look that can be paired with any outfit, both on and off the court. The Jordan 13 Retro in Wolf Gray was released on August 5th, 2023, for an initial price of $210.

The Air Jordan 13 French Blue features a white perforated leather upper with French Blue Durabuck mudguards and a grey leather toe wrap. Nodding to Michael Jordan's "Black Cat" nickname, a signature Jordan holographic emblem at the collar is reminiscent of panther eyes, while a sculptural sole takes the form of cat paws.

The Air Jordan 13 French Blue released in August of 2022 and retailed for $200.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro OG Chicago 2017 combines three colors; white, black, and true red. This sneaker’s look is influenced by the NBA team Chicago Bulls.

This 2017 Retro OG Air Jordan 13 features an upper crafted from 100% leather. The upper of this sneaker comes in a white hue and features some quilted overlays. The midsole, the heel, and the midfoot are dressed in red suede. The design is completed by a black sole and a Jumpman emblem, which also has a black hue.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro OG Chicago 2017 became available on 18th February 2017, its suggested retail price was $190.

The Jordan 13 Retro Flint is making its return in 2023, with the release of the Air Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint. ​
​
​The Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint is dressed in black, white, red, and Flint Grey. The Jordan 13 is constructed using leather, suede, and reflective mesh across the uppers. The sneakers are tied together with white laces, while a red Jumpman logo sits on top of the tongue. A holographic eye sits on the outer heel.
​​
​The Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint released April 22, 2023, with a retail price of $200.

name: Jordan 13 Retro Obsidian Powder Blue White

details.description:
Jordan Brand added Charlotte Hornets flair to their Fall 2021 line-up with the Air Jordan 13 Obsidian.

The Air Jordan 13 Obsidian arrives in similar color blocking as the renowned Jordan 13 He Got Game. It features a white tumbled leather upper with dark Obsidian underlays and a light blue Jumpman tongue embroidery. In traditional fashion, a holographic bubble on the ankle adds the finishing touch.

The Air Jordan 13 Obsidian released in September of 2021 and retailed for $190.

Jordan Brand geared up for springtime with the warm-toned Air Jordan 13 Del Sol.

At first glance, the Air Jordan 13 Del Sol looks like a flip of the 2018 Air Jordan 13 Carmelo Anthony Class of 2002. It features a white tumbled leather upper and golden yellow Durabuck underlays along the mudguard, accentuating its sculptural design. Hits of red on the Jumpman tongue embroideries pop against their white backdrop. At the collar, a signature Jumpman hologram completes the retro design.

The Air Jordan 13 Del Sol released in March of 2022 and retailed for $200.

After the hype of 2020's Air Jordan 13 Flint, Jordan Brand returned with a new colorway of the 1997 model later that year. The Air Jordan 13 Black Hyper Royal is reminiscent of former NBA All-Star Quinten Richardson’s Orlando Magic Player Edition (PE) colorway.

The Air Jordan 13 Black Hyper Royal is made in a familiar construction. The upper holds a mix of leather, mesh, and microfiber. The side panels sport reflective material, constructed with breathable mesh for ventilation. A holographic "23" badge on the ankle brings the sneaker to its original roots.

The Air Jordan 13 Black Hyper Royal released December 2020 for $190.

Paying homage to the cult-classic movie of the same name, the Jordan 13 Retro "He Got Game" is based on the pair Denzel Washington wore in the 1998 film. Directed by Spike Lee, Washington originally wore this pair of classic kicks while playing ball against his basketball prodigy son, Jesus Shuttlesworth (Ray Allen). The shoes feature a buttery leather upper in white and black, a green hologram on the side panel, and a red and white outsole. These dropped in August 2018 for $190. Do the right thing and grab a pair today on StockX.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro Black Cat, designed by Tinker Hatfield, was inspired by Michael Jordan nickname of "black cat".

This Retro Air Jordan 13 model has an upper that is built with suede material, finished in black, and overlaid by mesh, which sports a reflective finish. Rope laces secure the fit, while the Jumpman hologram logo marks the heel. Underfoot, there is a Zoom Air in the forefoot and heel of the Phylon midsole for cushioning, giving way to a herringbone panther's-paw outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro Black Cat was released on January 2017, at a retail price of $190.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro Wolf Grey (GS) is a grade-school-sized iteration of the iconic Jordan 13 silhouette, which is known for its unique and sleek design.

The shoes have a two-tone upper constructed using suede material with a leather shroud to cover the upper. It combines white and grey tones to give it a clean minimalist design aesthetic while the outsole is covered in red for a striking and vibrant appeal. Some distinctive details on the shoe include dimples on the leather shroud and a holographic eye on the lateral side of the ankle, both of which are synonymous with the Jordan 13 silhouette.

One thing we love about the shoes is the distinctive sole unit, which shares the shape of a panther’s paw print incorporating a pod system that provides targeted support, flexibility, and cushioning in specific areas of the foot. The Jordan 13 Retro Wolf Grey (GS) was released on the 5th of August, 2023, priced at $160.
